          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Situation A. Student Strategies</strong></p><p>The students in Mr. Satyam&#x27;s class used different strategies in the Initial Challenge to find the percent of sixth graders in the survey: 136 out of 400, who like having tacos for school lunch. </p><p>Examine the four strategies.</p><p>         1. How are the four students&#x27; strategies the same? Different? </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "iFNG6h4_UZLKJZcl",
        "title": "Text 4",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Both Suri and Zane used tape diagrams to solve the problem. Both Zane and Julia determine how many people 1% represents. Kelly scales the ratio to 100 people to write the percent. </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
