      {
        "id": "scCIJXMgJQX7YgfI",
        "title": "Text 2",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Situation B. Another Survey</strong></p><p>Another survey question asked:</p><ul><p>Do you want your school to sell T-shirts for a fundraiser?</p><p>The response was 117 out of 180 students said &quot;yes.&quot;</p></ul><p>What percent of students want to sell T-shirts? Explain your reasoning.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "k-y-ZzuL4WyK9Gco",
        "title": "Text 7",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Thinking like Suri:</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "abJZHoWCXaRnMSS6",
        "title": "Thinking like Suri",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Image",
          "url": "cq/images/thinking-like-suri.png",
          "filename": "cq/images/thinking-like-suri.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "g_XNenog_6iylVyR",
        "title": "Text 8",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>We can start at 50% to see if we need to go up or down to find what percent of 180 is 117. 50%: 90 students. 60%: 108 students. 70%: 126 students. Since 108 &lt; 117 &lt; 126, we know that 117 is between 60% and 70% of 180. 1% of 180 students is 1.8 students. 108 + 1.8(5) = 117, so 60% + 5% = 65% of students want to sell T-shirts.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "kQIr8xqE8INtkDe4",
        "title": "Text 9",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
